&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About Us&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to take the next step in your career? LAPORTE, a consulting engineering firm with 25 years of experience and a strong presence in North America and Europe, is seeking an&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Electrical Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join our growing team. With 25 offices and over 480 employees worldwide, we specialize in delivering innovative solutions for the pharmaceutical and food &amp;amp; beverage industries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At LAPORTE, we offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Salary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensatory Paid Time Off (PTO)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Flexible Work Environment&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;that values work-life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunities for Professional Growth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and become part of a supportive, collaborative team that encourages creativity and efficiency every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As an Electrical Engineer, you will lead and support electrical engineering requirements and construction packages for client projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and execute electrical design projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load list development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conductor sizing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overcurrent protective device (OCPD) sizing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lighting and switchgear design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cost estimates and equipment specification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee facility electrical design aspects including low-voltage facility electrical distribution systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Backup systems, grounding, fire alarms, lighting controls, and security systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with project teams while supervising and mentoring team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute full lifecycle project support, including system design, troubleshooting, testing, and commissioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct site surveys and provide on-site support during installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with relevant codes and standards (NEC, IBC, NFPA 101, ASHRAE, IECC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop project deliverables using AutoCAD and Revit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering or Electrical Engineering Technology required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EIT certification preferred; PE licensure is optional but a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5 years in manufacturing or consulting environments executing electrical power system design projects as a designer or design engineer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in managing medium-scale electrical projects, including client coordination, system design, and bid package preparation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with low-voltage (LV) systems design: lighting, fire alarm signaling, security systems, access control, etc. typical in MEP bid packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with distribution design: sizing/specifying equipment, conductors, and protection for LV/MV facility electrical distribution systems.&lt;/li&gt;
